    dc:creator "Vieira, Leandro M.; Gordon, Dennis P.; Souza, Facelucia B. C.; Haddad, Maria Angélica" ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "New and little-known cheilostomatous Bryozoa from the south and southeastern Brazilian continental shelf and slope" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.276534> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.276534>
    dc:description "FIGURES 77 – 82. Rhynchozoon coalitum n. sp., MZUSP 0 334 (part of the paratype specimen), off São Paulo, Brazil. 77, Fertile colony; 78, distal edge of colony; 79, close-up of autozooids, note the four oral spines; 80, close-up of ovicelled zooids, note the two oral spines; 81, close-up of orifice, note the four oral spines at the distal edge of orifice; 82, close-up of orifice with peristomial complex, noted the avicularium and adjacent mucro forming a labial pore." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/276534/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

